caption: Yummy!! Just happened upon it and the food and customer service was wonderful!
Great spot. Late night food, friendly staff, great drink prices.

Tomaso's is always a great experience whether you're up for good eats, or good drinks (or both). It's hard to compare what's better between the friendly, on-the-ball staff with the food that comes out of their kitchen. The food is 10/10. Fresh, made with care, delicious and totally enjoyable. Service is great and the food is no different. Love that you can grab eats til 1:00am for now!
Never disappointed!  Awesome little spot !

Really fantastic food.  Grossly understaffed.  The guy behind the bar deserves a bonus for running that place as well as he did (tattoos on knuckles, that guy).  Friendly service, attentive as he was able, given the number of customers, but his owners did him no favors by not scheduling enough help on a Sunday afternoon (unless he is the proprietor).  You should still go there and enjoy the food.  Seemed to have a generous beer selection, if that is your thing.  Do not bring any upright dinner companions who lose their minds if the service staff isn't asking how the table is every 5 minutes or less.  Go to enjoy the food and relax with a beverage.  Everything was fine for the patient-minded.

Those wings. Visiting from out of state and just wanted some comfort food after a snow storm that night; wouldn't you be surprised to find some of the best Buffalo Wings I've had in a long time. I did take out and they survived a ten minute drive and 20 minutes of savoring. If the rest of their menu is cooked with that much love then I can't to visit again.

I LOVE this place. From the outside it has a dive bar feel but it’s super cool inside. Great staff that has awesome beer recommendations. We came here while waiting to be seated at duck fat and I never wanted to leave.

Can't wait top go back and try the famous wings. Menu may not look extravagant but everything coming out of the kitchen looks awesome and what I've eaten tasted delicious. A bit too cozy for my taste but the food is worth it.

The ultimate hangout to flatten beers and wings with your crew! The wings here are absolutely perfect. Every sauce is exactly what you hope to have cross thine lips. $5 beers every Sunday during football, as if this little slice of heaven needed to get any better. Local drafts, all bangin. The “dirt” wings rebuffed are hands down the best wings I’ve ever had the pleasure of consuming. Can’t say enough about this local treasure. Included a picture of the homie on his birthday, just so you could see how much joy this establishment creates. 10/10

Tomaso's Canteen is a fantastic local dive bar in Portland. They have an outstanding selection of local craft beers and liquor. Plus, their food is much better than you would initially expect. Their Buffalo Wings are Dynamite and they make outstanding french fries.

Small place, 25 seats max I'd say. Food was good but this is moreso an elevated bar menu. Motha Clucka's app was simply delicious!! Although I wish you got more than 3 small Clucka's in the $8 basket. Buffalo chicken sandwich was a huge mess to eat. 4 breaded and tossed tenders on a hamburger bun with lettuce & tomatoes. I ended up having to eat the tenders separately since it doesn't stay together real well, which kind of defeats the purpose of a sandwich. The food was excellent, just not easy to handle without being a slob. Beer selection was great!! Bunker, Mason's, all kinds of local. Plus your standard Guinness, PBR and Narragansett and an array of liquors. Bartenders were fantastic too, I never waited more than a few seconds for anything (except food, obviously). Definitely will be back!

This local tucked away place is worth looking for. It's a small bar that offers both beer, wine well drinks and Pub food. The happy hour price is probably the best that I found in town Portland. Ice Pik Vodka drinks in a pint glass for $4... I'd say that's a killer deal for happy hour. This place is relatively small and can get crowded pretty quickly. But the food and the drinks are worth it!  My girlfriend and I had the tomasso burger. I really liked it, she thought it was a little spicy but overall I thought it was a great burger and reasonably priced.The bar staff was very helpful and attentive.  Don't make the mistake of parking in the parking lot in front of the building even after hours.  Easily within walking distance from most of the East End hotels in downtown Portland.

I have a new "go to" spot when visiting Portland.  Tomaso's packs a punch you would not expect from the outward appearance.  My wife and I walked up not sure if the place was even open, but once you open door - wow - the place was packed on a Sunday afternoon! We were lucky and another couple were leaving as we walked in and we scored a couple bar seats.   Tomaso's Canteen has an awesome selection of local and regional craft beer, wide array of specialty cocktails all with excellent in-house made sausage, flat top burgers and wings.  Try the mac & cheese sprinkled with bacon or the POOH wings - you will not be disappointed. They also have a selection of "beer and a shot" options, which we thought was great!  We will 100% be back... loved it.
